event.name: CORE week
event.description:
CORE is a Coding Oriented Realtime Event developed and organized by students at 42 
Heilbronn that blends the thrill of competition with the joy of learning and connection. It is a 
bot game coding challenge designed for programmers of all skill levels to test their abilities 
and compete in a dynamic tournament-style setting in 1vs1 matches. Whether you're a 
coding veteran or a curious beginner, CORE promises an exhilarating dive into the cosmos 
of C coding.  
 
This is the first time CORE Game is being played at multiple Campuses at the same time. 
Help us by joining this exciting Beta, take part in this thrilling competition and fight your 
peers. 
 
Find out more at coregame.de

event.name: Brownie Bakeoff
event.description:
All 42 students are invited to participate in a friendly brownie baking competition to discover whose brownie stands out as the best.
While there will be a secret prize awarded to the first-place winner, we encourage everyone to join primarily for the love of baking and the spirit of friendly competition. 
The judging panel will consist of three jurors representing each coalition. They will evaluate the brownies anonymously using a scoring system, ensuring that their focus remains solely on taste and quality. 
To participate, students must bake their brownies at home and submit a photo taken during the mixing process as proof of authenticity. Failure to provide this photographic evidence will result in disqualification from the competition. Make sure to submit the 
brownies on the day of the event before 2 pm at the kitchen on the second floor!  
Should this event prove successful, future competitions may offer enhanced rewards for winners.
We look forward to seeing your creativity and baking skills!

(for more information please reach out to @ombilica)

event.name: PISCINE COMMUNITY MEETING
event.description:
Coding all day (and night?) can be really stressful. To make sure we all have the chance to take a break and enjoy the community, we host community meetings once per week. Join us for some updates from the staff, some chitchat with your peers, and to simply enjoy the community instead of thinking about coding all the time :) We will also host a small Q&A session, giving you the chance to voice any concerns, or ask some questions you feel are left unanswered.

See you then! :)

event.name: GET TO KNOW CAMPUS FOUNDERS
event.description:
This is a special event we plan for you - A tour through the CampusFounders building and an introduction to their institution!

The CampusFounders are the Startup Hub of Heilbronn, and are part of our ecosystem. They are the go-to place for people interested in startups, and offer a variety of programs and events. During this event, you will get to know what they do and what they can offer, and also get a tour of their building. A must for anyone interested in the rapidly growing ecosystem in Heilbronn, and for anyone that is interested in startups or creating their own company.

Spots are limited to 50 people - If you register, you must attend. Please be on time!

Enjoy!
